Peru Consumer Prices Rose 0.27% in August From July, Government Says

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-09-01T06:35:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/peru-consumer-prices-rose-0-27-in-august-from-july-government-says.html
Peruvian consumer prices rose 0.27
percent in August compared with July, the National Statistics
Institute said in a statement published in the official gazette
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
